In general, any person who has been given authority to make arrests. Generally, a peace officer is a person designated by public authority to keep the peace and arrest persons guilty or suspected of crime and he is a conservator of the peace, which term is synonymous with the term peace officer. This term includes sheriffs and their deputies, member of the police force of cities, and other officers whose duty is to preserve the public peace. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Criminal Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_criminal/glossary.pdf)